i></ol></details></li><li class=\"toggle\"><details open=\"\"><summary>Instance methods</summary><ol><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Navigator/canShare\"><code>canShare()</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Navigator/clearAppBadge\"><code>clearAppBadge()</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Navigator/getAutoplayPolicy\"><code>getAutoplayPolicy()</code></a><abbr class=\"icon icon-experimental\" title=\"Experimental. Expect behavior to change in the future.\">\n    <span class=\"visually-hidden\">Experimental</span>\n</abbr></li><li><em><code>getBattery()</code> </em></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Navigator/getGamepads\"><code>getGamepads()</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Navigator/getInstalledRelatedApps\"><code>getInstalledRelatedApps()</code></a><abbr class=\"icon icon-experimental\" title=\"Experimental. Expect behavior to change in the future.\">\n    <span class=\"visually-hidden\">Experimental</span>\n</abbr></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Navigator/getUserMedia\"><code>getUserMedia()</code></a><abbr class=\"icon icon-deprecated\" title=\"Deprecated. Not for use in new websites.\">\n  <span class=\"visually-hidden\">Deprecated</span>\n</abbr></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Navigator/getVRDisplays\"><code>getVRDisplays()</code></a><abbr class=\"icon icon-nonstandard\" title=\"Non-standard. Check cross-browser support before using.\">\n    <span class=\"visually-hidden\">Non-standard</span>\n</abbr><abbr class=\"icon icon-deprecated\" title=\"Deprecated. Not for use in new websites.\">\n  <span class=\"visually-hidden\">Deprecated</span>\n</abbr></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Navigator/javaEnabled\"><code>javaEnabled()</code></a><abbr class=\"icon icon-deprecated\" title=\"Deprecated. Not for use in new websites.\">\n  <span class=\"visually-hidden\">Deprecated</span>\n</abbr></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Navigator/registerProtocolHandler\"><code>registerProtocolHandler()</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Navigator/requestMediaKeySystemAccess\"><code>requestMediaKeySystemAccess()</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Navigator/requestMIDIAccess\"><code>requestMIDIAccess()</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Navigator/sendBeacon\"><code>sendBeacon()</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Navigator/setAppBadge\"><code>setAppBadge()</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Navigator/share\"><code>share()</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Navigator/taintEnabled\"><code>taintEnabled()</code></a><abbr class=\"icon icon-deprecated\" title=\"Deprecated. Not for use in new websites.\">\n  <span class=\"visually-hidden\">Deprecated</span>\n</abbr></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Navigator/unregisterProtocolHandler\"><code>unregisterProtocolHandler()</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Navigator/vibrate\"><code>vibrate()</code></a></li></ol></details></li><li class=\"toggle\"><details open=\"\"><summary>Related pages for Battery API</summary><ol><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/BatteryManager\"><code>BatteryManager</code></a></li><li><em><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Navigator/getBattery\" aria-current=\"page\"><code>Navigator.getBattery()</code></a></em></li></ol></details></li></ol>","sidebarMacro":"APIRef","body":[{"type":"prose","value":{"id":null,"title":null,"isH3":false,"content":"<div class=\"notecard secure\" id=\"sect1\"><p><strong>Secure context:</strong> This feature is available only in <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/Security/Secure_Contexts\">secure contexts</a> (HTTPS), in some or all <a href=\"#browser_compatibility\">supporting browsers</a>.</p></div>\n<p>\n  The <strong><code>getBattery()</code></strong> method provides information about the system's battery.\n  It returns a battery promise, which resolves with a <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/BatteryManager\"><code>BatteryManager</code></a> object providing some properties to get the battery status also some events you can handle to monitor the battery status.\n  This implements the <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Battery_Status_API\">Battery Status API</a>; see that documentation for additional details, a guide to using the API, and sample code.\n</p>\n<p>Since Chrome 103, the <code>Navigator.getBattery()</code> method of <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Battery_Status_API\">Battery Status API</a> only expose to secure context.</p>\n<div class=\"notecard note\" id=\"sect2\">\n  <p><strong>Note:</strong> Access to this feature may be controlled by the <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/HTTP/Headers/Permissions-Policy\"><code>Permissions-Policy</code></a> directive <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/HTTP/Headers/Permissions-Policy/battery\"><code>battery</code></a>.</p>\n</div>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"syntax","title":"Syntax","isH3":false,"content":"<div class=\"code-example\"><p class=\"example-header\"><span class=\"language-name\">js</span></p><pre class=\"brush: js notranslate\"><code><span class=\"token function\">getBattery</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span>\n</code></pre></div>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"parameters","title":"Parameters","isH3":true,"content":"<p>None.</p>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"return_value","title":"Return value","isH3":true,"content":"<p>A <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Promise\"><code>Promise</code></a> that fulfills with a <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/BatteryManager\"><code>BatteryManager</code></a> object which you can use to get information about the battery's state.</p>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"exceptions","title":"Exceptions","isH3":true,"content":"<dl>\n  <dt id=\"notallowederror\"><a href=\"#notallowederror\"><code>NotAllowedError</code></a> <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/DOMException\"><code>DOMException</code></a></dt>\n  <dd>\n    <p>Use of this feature was blocked by a <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/HTTP/Permissions_Policy\">Permissions Policy</a>.</p>\n  </dd>\n  <dt id=\"securityerror\"><a href=\"#securityerror\"><code>SecurityError</code></a> <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/DOMException\"><code>DOMException</code></a></dt>\n  <dd>\n    <p>The User Agent does not expose battery information to insecure contexts and this method was called from an insecure context.</p>\n  </dd>\n</dl>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"examples","title":"Examples","isH3":false,"content":"<p>This example fetches the current charging state of the battery and establishes a handler for the <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/BatteryManager/chargingchange_event\" title=\"chargingchange\"><code>chargingchange</code></a> event, so that the charging state is recorded whenever it changes.</p>\n<div class=\"code-example\"><p class=\"example-header\"><span class=\"language-name\">js</span></p><pre class=\"brush: js notranslate\"><code><span class=\"token keyword\">let</span> batteryIsCharging <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token boolean\">false</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n\nnavigator<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">getBattery</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">then</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token parameter\">battery</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token operator\">=&gt;</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n  batteryIsCharging <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> battery<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>charging<span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n\n  battery<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">addEventListener</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token string\">\"chargingchange\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token operator\">=&gt;</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n    batteryIsCharging <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> battery<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>charging<span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n  <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>For more examples and details, see <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Battery_Status_API\">Battery Status API</a>.</p>"}},{"type":"specifications","value":{"title":"Specifications","id":"specifications","isH3":false,"specifications":[{"bcdSpecificationURL":"https://w3c.github.io/battery/#dom-navigator-getbattery","title":"Battery Status API"}],"query":"api.Navigator.getBattery"}},{"type":"browser_compatibility","value":{"title":"Browser compatibility","id":"browser_compatibility","isH3":false,"query":"api.Navigator.getBattery"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"see_also","title":"See also","isH3":false,"content":"<ul>\n  <li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Battery_Status_API\">Battery Status API</a></li>\n  <li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/HTTP/Headers/Permissions-Policy\"><code>Permissions-Policy</code></a> <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/HTTP/Headers/Permissions-Policy/battery\"><code>battery</code></a> directive</li>\n</ul>"}}],"toc":[{"text":"Syntax","id":"syntax"},{"text":"Examples","id":"examples"},{"text":"Specifications","id":"specifications"},{"text":"Browser compatibility","id":"browser_compatibility"},{"text":"See also","id":"see_also"}],"summary":"The getBattery() method provides information about the system's battery.\n  It returns a battery promise, which resolves with a BatteryManager object providing some properties to get the battery status also some events you can handle to monitor the battery status.\n  This implements the Battery Status API; see that documentation for additional details, a guide to using the API, and sample code.","popularity":0.0051,"modified":"2023-12-01T14:40:27.000Z","source":{"folder":"en-us/web/api/navigator/getbattery","github_url":"https://github.com/mdn/content/blob/main/files/en-us/web/api/navigator/getbattery/index.md","last_commit_url":"https://github.com/mdn/content/commit/cf05364b23bc44af37a350319a1dd47485746a9c","filename":"index.md"},"short_title":"getBattery()","parents":[{"uri":"/en-US/docs/Web","title":"References"},{"uri":"/en-US/docs/Web/API","title":"Web APIs"},{"uri":"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Navigator","title":"Navigator"},{"uri":"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Navigator/getBattery","title":"getBattery()"}],"pageTitle":"Navigator: getBattery() method - Web APIs | MDN","noIndexing":false}}